This suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions cryptography, number theory, and complexity theory, which are all related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.NT (Number Theory). The paper also discusses the efficiency and effectiveness of the proposed algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a conjecture about the upper bound on the number of subsets that has to be enumerated, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
